Alignment and Formatting Icons in the dashboard 17

Step 1. Format and alignment of the icons:



Click on the Home image then go to General - x position = 671, y position = 0, width = 100, height= 75

Scaling - Normal , background =Off.

Click on the Activity image  then go to General - x position = 830, y position = 0, width = 85, height= 75

Scaling - Normal, background = Off.

Click on the Mentor image then go to  General - x position = 976, y position = 0, width = 99, height= 85

Scaling - Normal, background = Off.

Click on the Mentee image then go to General - x position = 1122, y position = 0, width = 93, height= 85

Scaling - Normal, background = Off.

Text boxes for images:

Select Home - text box then type text 'Home' then format like below and do the same for Activity, Mentor, and Mentee like below screenshots.



For Alignment - 

Click on the Home textbox then go to General - x position = 755, y position = 0, width = 72, height= 78

Click on the Activity textbox then go to General - x position = 899, y position = 0, width = 89, height= 75

Click on the Mentor textbox then go to General - x position = 1060, y position = 0, width = 78, height= 77

Click on the Mentee textbox then go to General - x position = 1202, y position = 0, width = 78, height= 75

After you format and align the icons, you can get similar screenshot like below. If there is a little bit  difference in your dashboard, you should align them according to the screenshot below.


Step 2. To create line under the images, select Insert - Shape - Line as shown below.

To format the line go to

General - x position = 671, y position = 78, width = 609, height= 37

Line - line color = #118DFF, weight 10

Rotation- 90

follow the gif below.






Add a shape to a report:

https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/power-bi/create-reports/power-bi-reports-add-text-and-shapes
